results.name: Coefficients in expansion of E_4^(7/8).
comment: In general, for 0 < m < 1, the expansion of (E_4)^m is asymptotic to (-1)^(n+1) * m * 3^(2*m) * Gamma(1/3)^(18*m) * exp(Pi*sqrt(3)*n) / (2^(9*m) * Pi^(12*m) * Gamma(1-m) * n^(1+m)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 05 2018
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..425
mathematica: nmax = 20; CoefficientList[Series[(1 + 240*Sum[DivisorSigma[3,k]*x^k, {k, 1, nmax}])^(7/8), {x, 0, nmax}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jul 08 2017 *)
